request.description:
### QUERY PARAMETERS

**sort**

The parameter is intended for sorting programs - ```{route}?sort={sort}```.

*days_remaining* - time until *application_deadline*, in ascending order;

*days_remaining_descending* - time until *application_deadline*, in descending order;

*by_name* - by name;

*closed_programs* - firstly shows closed ones, then the rest, also sorted by *remaining* days;

*my_programs_only* - shows only programs that were created by the current user, also sorted by *days_remaining*;

*favourites_only* - shows only programs that were added by the current user to the *favorite_programs* list, also sorted by *days_remaining*

*views_ascending* - sorted by number of views, in ascending order

*views_descending* - sorted by number of views, in descending order

__

**scopes**

For searching a Program by *name*, *city.name*, *program_type.name*, *program_format.title*, *college.name*, *functions.title*, *industries.name* and *skills.name*,  the *search|like|%search_query%* has to be used

It is intended for getting data for the Current widget on the EL page -> Student Activity.
It's only available for El administrator.

### QUERY PARAMETERS:

*majors* - array of major class objects {id:1};

*grad_year* - graduation year. It can have a value from the current year to (the current year + 4);

*job_types* - array of Job Type class objects {id:1};

It is intended for getting data for the Activity Summary Chart widget on the EL page -> Student Activity. It's only available for El administrator.
It contains data over the last 11 months + the current one. It always displays data from August till July.


### QUERY PARAMETERS:
*majors* - array of major class objects {id:1};

*grad_year* -  graduation year. It can have a value from the current year to (the current year + 4);

*job_types* - array of Job Type class objects {id:1};

